semantics.ranking

Class ExplainedRankingFunction<I extends Interpretable>

  • Object
    • RankingFunction<I>
      • ExplainedRankingFunction<I>
  • Type Parameters:
    I - Interpretable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ExplainedRelationalRankingFunction

    public class ExplainedRankingFunction<I extends Interpretable>
extends RankingFunction<I>
    Extended version of RankingFunction that returns explanations for each evaluation. An evaluation tree is built with instances of Explanation.
    Author:
    Tobias Falke

      • getRank

        public int getRank(Conditional<I> c,
          Explanation exp)
        Returns the rank for a conditional, which is the difference between the rank of its verification and the rank of its antecedence. If the verification is ranked with RankingFunction.INFINITY, it is also the result.
